<div class="p-6 bg-primary text-content space-y-6">
  <div class="space-y-1">
    <h1 class="text-xl font-semibold">Focus-visible audit</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-content-secondary">
      Tab from the first field to the last. Every focusable item should show the
      same ring — a 2px <code>var(--color-info)</code> outline with a 1px offset,
      applied globally via <code>:focus-visible</code> and
      <code>var(--focus-outline)</code>. The "Focus CSS" column below still
      documents the original per-component rule for reference; annotations will
      be stripped once the rollout is verified.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="rounded-lg border border-tertiary bg-secondary/30 p-4 text-sm space-y-2">
    <div class="font-semibold">Testing modes (Chrome DevTools → Rendering)</div>
    <ul class="list-disc ps-5 space-y-1 text-content-secondary">
      <li><kbd>Cmd</kbd>/<kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>P</kbd> → <em>Show Rendering</em></li>
      <li>Emulate <strong>prefers-color-scheme</strong> → <code>dark</code> to verify dark mode</li>
      <li>Emulate <strong>forced-colors</strong> → <code>active</code> to verify Windows HCM (ring should use system <code>Highlight</code>)</li>
      <li>Emulate <strong>prefers-contrast</strong> → <code>more</code> to verify the 3px <code>currentColor</code> variant</li>
      <li>Keyboard tab through from row 1. Mouse-click rows — no ring should appear</li>
      <li>Zoom browser to 200% — ring stays visible and proportionate</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <style>
    .fv-audit code { @apply text-xs; }
    .fv-audit pre {
      @apply text-xs leading-snug text-content-secondary whitespace-pre-wrap break-words;
    }
    .fv-audit pre .sel { @apply text-content font-medium; }
  </style>

